08/08/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- A Turkish Army officer was killed in an attack on his home by the terrorist organisation Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK), authorities said Monday (7 August).
Two PKK members broke into the Sirnak home of non-commissioned officer Levent Cevikirnak, attacking him and his son Sunday night.
The son remains in serious condition.
In other news, three Turkish soldiers were injured in a landmine blast in the Hakkari province Monday.
The mine is believed to have been planted by the PKK.
Also Monday, police in Batman announced the detention of five men, suspected aides to PKK.
Police acted on a tip they had received.
(Sabah - 08/08/06;
Zaman, NTV - 07/08/06)
